dc_title_s: British India: northern part.; Cabul; Nepaul.
dc_description_s: Scales differ. Imprint derived from the atlas in which this state of the map was issued. Previous state issued in the 1817 edition of "A New General Atlas"; engraver's name removed. "Drawn & engraved for Thomson's New General Atlas." Numbered "43." Shows boundaries, rivers, deserts and principal settlements; colouring shows possession. Relief shown by hachures and shading. Greenwich meridian. 3 maps on 1 sheet : hand colored ; 16 x 15 to 35 x 60 cm on sheet 51 x 60 cm
